place.name: BARNINGHAM NORWOOD
place.gazetteerText: BARNINGHAM-NORWOOD, a parish in Erpingham district, Norfolk; 4½ miles ESE of Holt, and 16 ENE of Ryburgh r. station. Post Town, Holt, under Thetford. Acres, 834. Real property, £1,065. Pop., 30. Houses, 8. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in. the diocese of Norwich. Value, £156. Patron, Trustees of late W. H. Wyndham, Esq. The church has an ancient brass, and is tolerable. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
